    "# Ejemplo: Calcular $\\pi\\ \\ $ usando Monte-Carlo"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Podemos hacer el siguiente analisis:\n",
    "    \n",
    "Si tenemos un circulo de radio R = 1.0, dentro de un cuadrado de lado L = 2*R, la relacion entre las areás sera:\n",
    "    \n",
    "$\\dfrac{Area Circulo}{Area Cuadrado} = \\dfrac{\\pi * r^2}{4*r^2} = \\dfrac{\\pi}{4} $\n",
    "\n",
    "Por lo tanto:\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\pi = 4 * \\dfrac{Area Circulo}{Area Cuadrado}$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "skip"

    "# tomado de http://nbviewer.ipython.org/github/forero/ComputationalMethods/blob/master/notes/integration.ipynb\n",
    "def my_gauss(x):\n",
    "    return np.exp(-(x**2))\n",
    "min_x = -5.0\n",
    "max_x = 5.0\n",
    "x = np.linspace(min_x, max_x ,1000)\n",
    "gaussian = my_gauss(x)\n",
    "plt.plot(x,gaussian)"
   ]

    "## Ahora generamos 10000 números aleatorios"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "n_random = 10000\n",
    "random_x = np.random.rand(n_random) * (max_x - min_x) + min_x\n",
    "random_y = np.random.rand(n_random) * (max_y - min_y) + min_y"
   ]

    "Comparar con el valor teórico de esa integral"

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {

     "slide_type": "subslide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Ayuda\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2D integrals (usando Monte-Carlo)\n",
    "\n",
    "We will follow the path of Monte-Carlo integration for highly dimensional integrals.\n",
    "\n",
    "The principle is that to solve an integral in 2-D, we will generate a swarm of points in 3D within the intervals that we care: $x_{\\rm min}, x_{\\rm max}$, $y_{\\rm min}$, $y_{\\rm max}$, $f_{\\rm min}(x,y)$ and $f_{\\rm max}(x,y)$. "
   ]
  },

   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
